This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object segmentation tasks. It also involves deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) also suggests a possible fit in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the mention of high-resolution pixel-wise loss and predicted output label maps suggests a possible fit in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
